results.name: Number of finite sets of relatively prime positive integers > 1 with least common multiple n.
comment: a(n) depends only on the prime signature of n.
If n is in A000961, a(n)=0.
If n is in A006881, a(n)=2. (End)
If n = p^k*q, where p and q are distinct primes and k >= 1, then a(n) = 3*4^(k-1)-2^(k-1). - _Robert Israel_, Jun 07 2018
link: Robert Israel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
maple: f:= proc(n) g(sort(map(t -> t[2],ifactors(n)[2]))) end proc:
local nL, Cands, nC, Cons, i;
for i from 1 to nL do
for i from 1 to nops(Cons[1]) do
Consi:= map(proc(t) if member(Cons[1][i],t) then NULL else t minus Cons[1][1..i-1] fi end proc, Cons[2..-1]);
